# Code Quality Standards

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use Black for code formatting
- Use isort for import sorting
- Use flake8 for linting
- Maximum cyclomatic complexity: 10 per function
- Maximum function length: 50 lines
- Maximum class length: 200 lines

## Code Smells
- Avoid duplicate code (DRY principle)
- Avoid long parameter lists
- Avoid deep nesting (maximum 3 levels)
- Avoid magic numbers and strings
- Avoid global variables
- Avoid mutable default arguments

## Design Patterns
- Use appropriate design patterns:
  - Factory for object creation
  - Strategy for algorithms
  - Observer for event handling
  - Singleton for global state
  - Command for operations
- Keep SOLID principles in mind:
  - Single Responsibility
  - Open/Closed
  - Liskov Substitution
  - Interface Segregation
  - Dependency Inversion

## Code Reviews
- Review for:
  - Functionality
  - Performance
  - Security
  - Maintainability
  - Testability
- Provide constructive feedback
- Document review decisions

## Refactoring
- Regular refactoring sessions
- Keep technical debt low
- Improve code quality incrementally
- Document major refactoring decisions
- Maintain backward compatibility
